@startuml C4_Pattern_MessageQueue
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Workflow Pattern - Message-Driven Workflow

Boundary(message_source, "Message Sources") {
    Component(producer1, "Producer 1", "System", "System A")
    Component(producer2, "Producer 2", "System", "System B")
    Component(producer3, "Producer 3", "System", "User action")
}

Boundary(message_broker, "Message Broker") {
    Component(kafka, "Kafka/RabbitMQ", "Broker", "Message queue")
    Component(topic_priority, "Topic: Priority", "Queue", "Urgent messages")
    Component(topic_normal, "Topic: Normal", "Queue", "Regular messages")
    Component(topic_dlq, "Topic: DLQ", "Queue", "Dead letter queue")
}

Boundary(workflow_mgmt, "Workflow Management") {
    Component(message_listener, "MessageListener", "Subscribe", "Listen to topics")
    Component(message_mapper, "MessageMapper", "Transform", "Message → task input")
    Component(message_task, "MessageTask", "Task", "Process message")
    Component(message_handler, "MessageHandler", "Logic", "Business logic")
}

Boundary(routing, "Message Routing") {
    Component(priority_queue, "PriorityQueue", "Urgent", "Process first")
    Component(normal_queue, "NormalQueue", "Regular", "FIFO order")
    Component(retry_logic, "RetryLogic", "Error", "Retry on failure")
}

producer1 --> kafka: Publishes
producer2 --> kafka: Publishes
producer3 --> kafka: Publishes

kafka --> topic_priority: High priority
kafka --> topic_normal: Normal
kafka --> topic_dlq: Failed

message_listener --> priority_queue: Listens to priority
message_listener --> normal_queue: Listens to normal
priority_queue --> message_mapper: Maps message
normal_queue --> message_mapper: Maps message
message_mapper --> message_task: Invokes task
message_task --> message_handler: Executes
retry_logic --> topic_dlq: On max retries

Note as N1
Message-Driven Pattern:
1. Messages published to broker
2. Multiple topics by priority
3. Workflow listens to topics
4. Map messages to task inputs
5. Execute workflow task
6. Retry on failure
7. Dead-letter queue for failures

Advantages:
- Asynchronous processing
- Decoupled systems
- Scalable
- Fault-tolerant
- Audit trail (all messages logged)
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
